        "timestamp": "2021-08-04 01:28:15.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-2\n\nI just realized that because the logging files were being moved to policy/common - ONAPLogging project, the EELF library is reintroduced as it is one of the dependencies, check out the pom.xml.   In turn, that library it has the potential to hijack logging in the classpath wherever the ONAPLogging library is used.\n\nThe solution is to revert the common review and move those under policy-common utils project (or a non invasive one) instead of the onap logging.\n\nSorry, I didn't realize that when I saw your policy/common review.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
